151
00:08:24.536 --> 00:08:28.396
And I'll start with some definitions of how we evaluate

152
00:08:28.456 --> 00:08:29.556
clinical trials.

153
00:08:30.776 --> 00:08:31.456
Efficacy,

154
00:08:32.376 --> 00:08:35.856
this is the extent to which an intervention is more beneficial than

155
00:08:35.956 --> 00:08:38.716
harmful under ideal circumstances.

156
00:08:39.586 --> 00:08:43.136
While effectiveness is whether an intervention is more

157
00:08:43.196 --> 00:08:46.816
beneficial than harmful under conditions of

158
00:08:47.216 --> 00:08:48.636
real, everyday practice.

159
00:08:49.456 --> 00:08:52.796
Efficiency, on the other hand, this is the effect of an

160
00:08:52.836 --> 00:08:55.656
intervention in relation to the resources it needs.

161
00:08:56.696 --> 00:09:00.276
But for all of us, for patients, for oncologists, the key question is:

162
00:09:00.856 --> 00:09:04.736
Will this treatment work for the patient that I'm seeing in the office

163
00:09:04.796 --> 00:09:05.236
today?

164
00:09:06.656 --> 00:09:08.396
And this is what pragmatic trials are.

165
00:09:08.416 --> 00:09:09.236
They are designed

166
00:09:10.356 --> 00:09:13.856
to inform decision maker about the effectiveness, the

167
00:09:13.916 --> 00:09:16.836
balance of benefits, burdens, and risk of an

168
00:09:16.896 --> 00:09:18.356
intervention in

169
00:09:19.176 --> 00:09:22.636
routine clinical practice. This is in contrast

170
00:09:22.756 --> 00:09:26.616
to the explanatory, more traditional type of trial

171
00:09:26.676 --> 00:09:29.776
that tests the efficacy under ideal conditions.

172
00:09:30.306 --> 00:09:33.586
So a pragmatic trial asks the question, does this

173
00:09:33.636 --> 00:09:36.396
intervention work under usual conditions?

174
00:09:37.456 --> 00:09:41.426
And the opportunity to use pragmatic trial approach for registrational

175
00:09:41.496 --> 00:09:44.476
intents is clearly novel and potentially

176
00:09:44.896 --> 00:09:46.156
paradigm changing.

177
00:09:49.516 --> 00:09:49.916
Usually,

178
00:09:51.136 --> 00:09:53.916
pragmatic and explanatory trials are looked at

179
00:09:54.896 --> 00:09:58.736
very independently as two extremes, on one side,

180
00:09:58.836 --> 00:10:00.616
pragmatic, on the other side, explanatory.

181
00:10:01.376 --> 00:10:04.796
And from this figure from Lancet Oncology,

182
00:10:06.096 --> 00:10:09.936
it is clear that it's a continuum. There is a lot of overlap,

183
00:10:10.336 --> 00:10:14.176
and this can be on patient selection, it can be on the intervention,

184
00:10:14.536 --> 00:10:18.236
it can be outcomes, whether it's very standardized,

185
00:10:18.276 --> 00:10:21.976
intermediate for the explanatory or clear,

186
00:10:24.276 --> 00:10:28.136
definitive for the pragmatic overall survival

187
00:10:28.236 --> 00:10:29.836
versus response rate,

188
00:10:30.836 --> 00:10:34.296
the data elements that are being collected, the

189
00:10:34.336 --> 00:10:34.976
comparator.

190
00:10:35.936 --> 00:10:39.236
So it's a continuum. There is no purely pragmatic or purely

191
00:10:39.276 --> 00:10:40.116
explanatory.

192
00:10:41.236 --> 00:10:45.216
The design of pragmatic trials were really

193
00:10:45.276 --> 00:10:49.116
accelerated when Project Pragmatica was launched by

194
00:10:49.176 --> 00:10:50.536
the FDA

195
00:10:52.016 --> 00:10:54.296
at the leadership of Dr. Pozdner, who is here,

196
00:10:55.516 --> 00:10:59.296
looking at functional efficiencies and enhanced patient

197
00:10:59.416 --> 00:11:03.156
centricity. So the idea was to do

198
00:11:03.236 --> 00:11:05.776
pragmatic trial designs that incorporate

199
00:11:06.816 --> 00:11:10.596
aspects of traditional clinical trials, but with real-world

200
00:11:11.396 --> 00:11:15.316
and routine clinical practice elements, depending on the

201
00:11:15.376 --> 00:11:19.216
disease under question, knowledge about the treatment, and other practical and

202
00:11:19.276 --> 00:11:21.096
scientific considerations.

203
00:11:22.616 --> 00:11:24.636
So we launched Pragmatica Lung

204
00:11:25.196 --> 00:11:28.996
S2302 as a prospective randomized study of

205
00:11:29.716 --> 00:11:33.536
a chemotherapy-free regimen, ramucirumab and pembrolizumab,

206
00:11:33.616 --> 00:11:37.456
versus standard of care chemotherapy for patients with previously treated

207
00:11:37.676 --> 00:11:38.356
lung cancer.

208
00:11:39.196 --> 00:11:42.196
This was an FDA registrational intent trial.

209
00:11:44.496 --> 00:11:48.396
It emerged as a way to validate

210
00:11:48.406 --> 00:11:51.756
the overall survival benefit of a smaller

211
00:11:51.796 --> 00:11:55.296
randomized Phase 2 trial, S1800A, that was done

212
00:11:55.796 --> 00:11:57.816
in the Lung-MAP platform.

213
00:11:58.856 --> 00:12:02.716
These results needed to be validated, and we wanted to design a

214
00:12:02.736 --> 00:12:05.336
pragmatic trial to reduce the burden

215
00:12:06.356 --> 00:12:10.256
of clinical trial participation and to promote inclusion of all participants

216
00:12:10.316 --> 00:12:14.276
with the disease. So our goals were to empower investigators

217
00:12:14.356 --> 00:12:18.236
to treat patients on the trial as they would in the real world, to

218
00:12:18.276 --> 00:12:21.516
decrease barriers to enrollment, and to minimize data

219
00:12:21.596 --> 00:12:25.264
collection.It was a

220
00:12:25.404 --> 00:12:27.594
very straightforward, simple design.

221
00:12:27.884 --> 00:12:29.984
Patients with previously treated lung cancer

222
00:12:30.824 --> 00:12:33.884
were randomized to receive either standard of care

223
00:12:34.924 --> 00:12:36.864
or remicirumab and pembrolizumab.

224
00:12:38.504 --> 00:12:41.584
Eight hundred participants were planned to be enrolled.

225
00:12:42.504 --> 00:12:46.244
There was a single primary objective, overall survival, and

226
00:12:46.404 --> 00:12:48.204
only two secondary objectives,

227
00:12:49.404 --> 00:12:53.224
serious and unexpected high-grade treatment-related adverse events

228
00:12:53.764 --> 00:12:55.884
and survival comparison by histology.

229
00:12:57.724 --> 00:13:00.664
With this simplified concept,

230
00:13:01.854 --> 00:13:05.124
the protocol was developed from concept to

231
00:13:05.134 --> 00:13:08.684
activation in 200 days. And as a reminder,

232
00:13:09.344 --> 00:13:10.004
the guidelines

233
00:13:10.864 --> 00:13:14.664
recommend a target of 300 days and a deadline

234
00:13:14.824 --> 00:13:16.544
of 540 days.

235
00:13:17.604 --> 00:13:18.564
And the protocol

236
00:13:19.604 --> 00:13:23.284
was 47 pages. Now, if we exclude

237
00:13:23.304 --> 00:13:26.864
appendices, it becomes 30 pages, and this is a Phase 3

238
00:13:26.884 --> 00:13:30.664
registrational intent trial. Informed consent form was 11 pages.

239
00:13:31.104 --> 00:13:34.344
So these are less than half of what the smaller

240
00:13:34.664 --> 00:13:36.364
randomized Phase 2 trial was.

241
00:13:39.864 --> 00:13:43.824
A very short timeline. The results of the Phase 2

242
00:13:43.904 --> 00:13:44.284
trial

243
00:13:45.264 --> 00:13:48.744
became available early 2022. We submitted

244
00:13:49.244 --> 00:13:52.044
for presentation at ASCO in February 2022.

245
00:13:52.944 --> 00:13:56.624
There was an oral presentation and simultaneous JCO publication in June.

246
00:13:57.184 --> 00:14:00.844
Within a month, we started talking about Pragmatic Lung.

247
00:14:02.224 --> 00:14:06.064
In March of 2023, Pragmatic Lung launched, and in December of

248
00:14:06.164 --> 00:14:09.604
2024, it completed accrual. This

249
00:14:09.664 --> 00:14:13.604
is a very unusually short timeline for a Phase 3 trial.

250
00:14:16.144 --> 00:14:19.744
The trial showed no difference in overall survival for the

251
00:14:19.824 --> 00:14:23.744
chemotherapy-free remicirumab pembrolizumab combination compared

252
00:14:23.784 --> 00:14:24.704
to standard of care,

253
00:14:25.764 --> 00:14:29.744
with a decrease in adverse events, serious adverse

254
00:14:29.784 --> 00:14:33.504
events leading to discontinuation with the chemotherapy-free

255
00:14:33.704 --> 00:14:37.624
arm, and a trend towards increase in time to treatment

256
00:14:37.724 --> 00:14:38.123
failure.

257
00:14:40.144 --> 00:14:40.364
This

258
00:14:41.264 --> 00:14:44.764
rapid design and completion of the trial was clearly

259
00:14:44.804 --> 00:14:46.844
facilitated by the pragmatic design.

260
00:14:48.224 --> 00:14:49.244
There were very few

261
00:14:51.864 --> 00:14:53.524
limited eligibility criteria,

262
00:14:54.964 --> 00:14:55.424
stage,

263
00:14:56.624 --> 00:15:00.264
prior therapy, performance status, and safety in terms of ability to

264
00:15:00.324 --> 00:15:03.784
receive the treatment. Patients were enrolled and treated as

265
00:15:03.824 --> 00:15:07.164
we do in everyday practice. The

266
00:15:07.324 --> 00:15:10.564
only recommendation was use institutional guidelines and

267
00:15:10.644 --> 00:15:12.304
investigator discretion.

268
00:15:13.424 --> 00:15:17.304
There was minimal items on the study calendar, no study

269
00:15:17.344 --> 00:15:19.124
required labs, no imaging.

270
00:15:20.564 --> 00:15:24.124
The data that we wanted to capture was minimized to

271
00:15:24.204 --> 00:15:27.844
reduce the time points to be collected, the number of

272
00:15:27.904 --> 00:15:29.164
forms, and the number of

273
00:15:30.544 --> 00:15:34.394
data elements per form. There are

274
00:15:34.444 --> 00:15:37.244
no concurrent medications being collected, and this

275
00:15:37.524 --> 00:15:40.784
simplified the monitoring auditing of the trial.

276
00:15:43.984 --> 00:15:46.984
We had very rapid accrual and broad

277
00:15:47.404 --> 00:15:50.424
representatives as a result of the pragmatic design.

278
00:15:50.904 --> 00:15:53.064
On the left is the accrual

279
00:15:53.924 --> 00:15:56.994
curve. The dotted line is the

280
00:15:57.924 --> 00:16:01.744
targeted accrual when we designed the trial, 29 patients per

281
00:16:03.224 --> 00:16:07.184
month. And as you can see throughout the life of the trial,

282
00:16:07.444 --> 00:16:11.324
we enrolled clearly more patients, between 40 and 60.

283
00:16:11.784 --> 00:16:15.204
And usually, when we show graphs like this, they are reversed.

284
00:16:15.354 --> 00:16:18.843
The targeted is much higher than the accrual.

285
00:16:19.354 --> 00:16:23.204
And the accruals came from the entire NCTN

286
00:16:23.264 --> 00:16:26.984
network of community and academic sites in

287
00:16:27.224 --> 00:16:30.924
rural and urban area, not just the ivory

288
00:16:30.964 --> 00:16:34.184
tower academic centers, with more than

289
00:16:34.484 --> 00:16:38.304
600 sites having the study open. This led to a

290
00:16:38.364 --> 00:16:41.324
very broad representativeness of the

291
00:16:41.364 --> 00:16:43.464
participants that enrolled.

292
00:16:46.384 --> 00:16:50.284
And our goal of reducing the burden of clinical

293
00:16:50.384 --> 00:16:53.644
trial participation is very clearly demonstrated

294
00:16:53.744 --> 00:16:57.704
here. This is the dramatic reduction

295
00:16:57.804 --> 00:17:01.384
in the number of data elements collected at one year

296
00:17:02.624 --> 00:17:05.565
and the number of forms submitted at one year

297
00:17:06.024 --> 00:17:09.404
compared to the very similarly designed smaller

298
00:17:09.864 --> 00:17:13.744
Phase 2, S1800A. So the design

299
00:17:13.825 --> 00:17:14.604
clearly worked.

300
00:17:17.204 --> 00:17:19.565
It is not a design for every trial.

301
00:17:20.684 --> 00:17:23.384
We had agents with known toxicities.

302
00:17:24.744 --> 00:17:26.704
The combination was already studied.

303
00:17:30.084 --> 00:17:33.524
In the era of precision oncology, complex studies

304
00:17:33.844 --> 00:17:37.644
typically limit patients accrual in the single trial, so we were offering a

305
00:17:37.824 --> 00:17:41.284
very broad eligibility opportunities.

306
00:17:42.204 --> 00:17:42.764
We had

307
00:17:43.924 --> 00:17:47.664
both NCI and the FDA launching initiatives to promote

308
00:17:47.724 --> 00:17:51.494
pragmatic trial design. We had very strong support from the Friends of

309
00:17:51.564 --> 00:17:53.624
Cancer Research and the Foundation of NIH.

310
00:17:54.724 --> 00:17:58.204
And clinical centers and research sites really

311
00:17:58.764 --> 00:18:01.764
interested in finding ways to enhance patient accrual.

312
00:18:03.084 --> 00:18:06.924
So what we learned from Pragmatic Lung was that patients do want to

313
00:18:06.984 --> 00:18:10.424
enroll in clinical trials, but features of standard

314
00:18:10.484 --> 00:18:13.684
explanatory trials often present barriers to participation.

315
00:18:14.584 --> 00:18:18.484
Pragmatic Lung set a paradigm-shifting example in

316
00:18:18.524 --> 00:18:22.314
trial conduct that should be applied to future randomized

317
00:18:22.404 --> 00:18:25.224
trials, including those with registrational

318
00:18:25.284 --> 00:18:29.224
intent.The pragmatic elements of the trial led to

319
00:18:29.324 --> 00:18:33.304
faster protocol development of activation with less burden

320
00:18:33.364 --> 00:18:34.364
on research staff.

321
00:18:36.044 --> 00:18:39.224
Pragmatic Lung achieved rapid accrual among

322
00:18:39.324 --> 00:18:42.824
representative patient population, leading to generalizable

323
00:18:42.884 --> 00:18:43.324
results.

324
00:18:44.304 --> 00:18:48.264
So thoughtfully including pragmatic elements in trials

325
00:18:48.904 --> 00:18:51.844
will provide increased access for patients.

326
00:18:53.544 --> 00:18:54.364
I would like to thank

327
00:18:55.344 --> 00:18:59.104
the study participants in Pragmatic Lung, their caregivers,

328
00:18:59.264 --> 00:19:03.024
the research site, as well as the FDA, NCI CTEP,

